content: For cream-colored rugs, you can check out websites like Wayfair, West Elm, and Rugs USA. These sites offer a wide variety of styles and sizes, and you're sure to find something that would work well in your space. As for natural wood accents, you could look at stores like Crate and Barrel, Pottery Barn or even Ikea. These stores offer a range of wood furniture and decor items that could work well in a space with forest green and burnt orange. You could also try shopping at local home decor stores or even flea markets for unique, one-of-a-kind wood pieces that could add character to your space. It's always a good idea to compare prices and read reviews before making any purchases to ensure you're getting the best value for your money. Good luck with your shopping!
